Martin Reverby, better known by his stage name Martin Rev, (born December 18, 1947) is an American musician and one half of the influential synth-punk band Suicide.
He contributed to the Raveonettes' 2005 album, Pretty in Black.
In 2008, while Martin was working on the album Stigmata, his wife Mari died.

"Demolition 9 is New York electronic music pioneer Martin Rev’s ninth solo album, and first new material since 2009.

Composed of 34 wildly divergent vignettes – only one of which reaches three minutes in length – he describes it as autobiographical “yearning for joy and the unattainable perfection of the artistic ideal.”"
